                            <comment id="12540999" author="udanax" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2007 08:49:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey, michael.&lt;br/&gt;
Is it okay to upload php extension module to svn?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12541188" author="stack" created="Fri, 9 Nov 2007 00:33:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chatting with Edward, this patch ups up an IPC server that takes in HQL strings, parses them, and then does HTable&apos;ing of the parsed query over to a hbase cluster.  It includes a client to test the IPC server written in java but he also has a php client for the IPC server.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12541271" author="udanax" created="Fri, 9 Nov 2007 09:52:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To support (non-java) client, protocols will be defined and developed in socket server.&lt;br/&gt;
And i&apos;ll upload with c++/php example scripts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542082" author="udanax" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2007 09:23:52 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Echo test between a java server and a php client&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In a next patch, I&apos;ll change the shell&apos;s outputting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542740" author="udanax" created="Thu, 15 Nov 2007 11:03:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;see : &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/lucene-hadoop/Hbase/HbaseShell/PHP&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/lucene-hadoop/Hbase/HbaseShell/PHP&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542741" author="udanax" created="Thu, 15 Nov 2007 11:07:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I want to develop the linux shell script for server start.&lt;br/&gt;
Shoul it be put into hbase-start.sh?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542791" author="stack" created="Thu, 15 Nov 2007 15:10:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No.  This feature is an option that will, IMO, be used infrequently.  The hbase start scripts are already crowded.  It would be better to have your own start script.  It could sit beside all other hbase scripts in bin but you might want to make it independent of any direct hbase dependencies &amp;#8211; i.e. not have it source other hbase scripts &amp;#8211; so this feature can be installed apart from an hbase install.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542811" author="stack" created="Thu, 15 Nov 2007 16:13:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Edward: Have you considered having your clients making HTTP requests against the HQL page in the master webapp?  It wouldn&apos;t be as fast as having your clients go via IPC but it&apos;d be easier to develop and maintain.  If you want, we can move the HQL page out of the master webapp and add it to a new hql webapp that could be deployed by default at the master but that could also be deployed elsewhere should the HQL requests threaten to overwhelm the master.  The hql webapp. could leveage the REST webapp work over at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-269&quot; title=&quot;[hbase] RESTful interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-269&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-2068&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542929" author="udanax" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2007 01:41:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Have you considered having your clients making HTTP requests against the HQL page in the master webapp? It wouldn&apos;t be as fast as having your clients go via IPC but it&apos;d be easier to develop and maintain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This method won&apos;t be easy to use and slow, too. Also, to use it, Tomcat must be installed and &lt;br/&gt;
Tomcat is used for WebServer. Shell Server will be implemented to optimize the return of the query results. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I think hql.jsp has no reason to be objected. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542931" author="udanax" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2007 01:53:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;And i think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-269&quot; title=&quot;[hbase] RESTful interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-269&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-2068&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is different issue from it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12542954" author="udanax" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2007 04:57:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://shell.hadoop.co.kr/PHPClient.php&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://shell.hadoop.co.kr/PHPClient.php&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can see the example by clicking the link above.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12545324" author="udanax" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2007 03:43:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t commit, so i&apos;m wait your vote.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12548041" author="udanax" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2007 23:10:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Guys, it&apos;s my very poor question.&lt;/p&gt;

